				\begin{document}$${Er}_{i}= {TR}_{i}\bullet {CF}_{i}$$\end{document}Eri=TRi∙CFiwhere TRi is the toxic response factor and CFi is a contamination factor of a particular heavy element. The values of the toxic response factor TR were adopted from the literature (Liu et al., 2021; Saha et al., 2022; Turhun & Eziz, 2022). Potential ecological risk index (RI) is defined as\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
